From: Ryan Chen <rchen14b@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: phy: realtek: rtl826x: fix interrupt handler for
 irqbalance compatibility

The rtl826x_handle_intr() function returns IRQ_NONE when MDIO operations
fail. This causes problems when irqbalance migrates the IRQ to another
CPU, as MDIO bus operations can transiently fail during migration.

When IRQ_NONE is returned repeatedly, the kernel's spurious interrupt
detection triggers "irq XX: nobody cared" and disables the IRQ entirely,
breaking PHY link change detection.

Fix this by:
1. Always returning IRQ_HANDLED since the interrupt definitely came from
   this PHY (it's level-triggered and asserts until acknowledged)
2. Logging MDIO failures for debugging rather than bailing out
3. Continuing to process what we can even after partial failures

This ensures the PHY interrupt remains functional even with irqbalance
enabled, while still properly handling link change and PME events when
MDIO operations succeed.

Signed-off-by: Ryan Chen <rchen14b@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/net/phy/realtek/realtek_main.c | 35 ++++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 27 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/phy/realtek/realtek_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/phy/realtek/realtek_main.c
@@ -2356,14 +2356,24 @@ static int rtl826x_config_intr(struct ph
 
 static irqreturn_t rtl826x_handle_intr(struct phy_device *phydev)
 {
-	u32 data;
+	int data;
 
 	data = phy_read_mmd(phydev, MDIO_MMD_VEND2, RTL826X_VND2_INSR);
-	if (data < 0)
-		return IRQ_NONE;
+	if (data < 0) {
+		/*
+		 * MDIO read can fail transiently when irqbalance migrates
+		 * the IRQ to another CPU. Return IRQ_HANDLED to prevent
+		 * the kernel from disabling this IRQ due to "nobody cared".
+		 * The interrupt is level-triggered and will re-assert if
+		 * there's a real pending event.
+		 */
+		phydev_dbg(phydev, "INSR read failed: %d\n", data);
+		return IRQ_HANDLED;
+	}
 
+	/* Clear interrupt status - continue even if this fails */
 	if (phy_modify_mmd(phydev, MDIO_MMD_VEND1, 0x2DC, GENMASK(15, 0), 0xFF) < 0)
-		return IRQ_NONE;
+		phydev_dbg(phydev, "Failed to clear interrupt status\n");
 
 	if (data & RTL826X_VND2_INER_LINK_STATUS) {
 		phydev_dbg(phydev, "RTK_PHY_INTR_LINK_CHANGE\n");
@@ -2373,11 +2383,15 @@ static irqreturn_t rtl826x_handle_intr(s
 	if (data & RTL826X_VND2_INER_PME) {
 		phydev_dbg(phydev, "RTK_PHY_INTR_WOL\n");
 
-		if (phy_modify_mmd(phydev, MDIO_MMD_VEND2, 0xD8A2, BIT(15), 0) < 0)
-			return IRQ_NONE;
-
-		if (phy_modify_mmd(phydev, MDIO_MMD_VEND2, 0xD8A2, BIT(15), 1 << 15) < 0)
-			return IRQ_NONE;
+		if (phy_modify_mmd(phydev, MDIO_MMD_VEND2, 0xD8A2, BIT(15), 0) < 0) {
+			phydev_dbg(phydev, "Failed to clear PME status (step 1)\n");
+			return IRQ_HANDLED;
+		}
+
+		if (phy_modify_mmd(phydev, MDIO_MMD_VEND2, 0xD8A2, BIT(15), 1 << 15) < 0) {
+			phydev_dbg(phydev, "Failed to clear PME status (step 2)\n");
+			return IRQ_HANDLED;
+		}
 	}
 
 	return IRQ_HANDLED;
